Given the confusion in the literature, we first set out to define independence and exclusivity of events through their joint probability. Assume there are n statistical hypotheses, and H1, …, Hn are events corresponding to each hypothesis being true. These hypotheses are tested using some observations y or a random variable Y representing the state of the dynamical system. In what follows we use a short-hand notation Y to mean the event of observing the underlying random variable Y taking a value of y. Joint probability of two hypotheses Hi and Hj given the observations is defined as1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
