				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{array}{*{20}{l}} {P\left( {H_i \cap H_j|{\bf{Y}}} \right).} \hfill \end{array}$$\end{document}PHi∩Hj∣Y .

If these hypotheses are conditionally independent given Y, the joint probability is the product of the conditional probabilities9:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
