Evaluating the terms in the full BMA equation (Eq. (7)) is non-trivial. However, if our hypotheses can be defined by some parameters θ belonging to regions in parameter space, the problem simplifies. Specifically, we can use the marginalization theorem to obtain8\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
